        (111503, 'True Lies', 1994, 2710, 7, 1919, 115000000, 378882411, 'Harry Tasker is a secret agent for the United States Government. For years, he has kept his job from his wife, but is forced to reveal his identity and try to stop nuclear terrorists when he and his wife are kidnapped by them.', '/o2agns0LEqyEUCByMT8ViIOio7r.jpg', '/9yOzwgGdVoRhDYSwVbhyhgNMoUi.jpg', 0),
        (111653, 'Wagons East!', 1994, 67632, 5, 39, 0, 0, 'After the 1860s Wild West, a group of misfit settlers - including ex-doctor Phil Taylor, prostitute Belle, and homosexual bookseller Julian - decide they cannot live in their current situation in the west. They hire a grizzled alcoholic wagon master by the name of James Harlow to take them on a journey back to their hometowns in the East.', '/5uf31DQxAFPtveULkEC8a70iPQA.jpg', '/8Q9ulJq69kO6nT1Xs5XnL0dDjje.jpg', 0),
        (111666, 'War of the Buttons', 1994, 120218, 7, 49, 0, 0, 'The children of Ballydowse and Carrickdowse engage in battles where they cut of the buttons, shoe-laces and underwear of their captured opponents. This is to get the boys in trouble with their parents. They go to battle in mass groups of dozens, throwing stones and cutting off their opponents buttons etc. And sometimes they go to battle completely naked and exposed. In one such scene about 30 boys return from a battle to celebrate victory at a barn-house only to find some girls waiting for them and they get very embarrassed at losing their privacy', '/yIpH14eEMJr9siW7bSAYTs9tLPR.jpg', '/kpVvrfK2klW8netmZt9UUYlbLYh.jpg', 0),
